                        <title xml:lang="en">A commentary on Numbers</title>
                        
                        
                        
                        <note>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Includes Numbers 1:1-3:51, 4:21-5:31 - the pointed and accentuated Hebrew text, an Arabic translation and a short commentary of apparently Abu al-Faraj Furḳan.</p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>The Hebrew text is arrnged into sections: Numbers 1:1-54, 2:1-34, 3:1-51, 4:21-49, 5:1-4, 5-10, 11-31.</p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>An Arabic translation is added to each verse, and each section is followed by the corresponding portion of the commentary.</p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Has scant masoretic notes.</p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Quotes several Karaite authorities.</p>
                        
                        
                        
                        </note>
                        
                        
                        
                        <author>
                           
                           
                           
                           <persName xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf.org/viaf/58767269">Abu al-Faraj Furḳan, active 11th century <addName>Jeshua ben Judah </addName>
                           
                           
                           
                           </persName>
                           
                           
                           
                           <persName xml:lang="he" key="viaf.org/viaf/58767269">ישועה בן יהודה </persName>
                        
                        
                        
                        </author>
                        
                        
                        
                        <filiation>The translation is in agreement with Or. 2491, George Margoliouth, Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, 4 vols (London: British Museum, 1899-1935; vols I-III repr. 1965); IV, Introduction, Indexes, ed. by Jacob Leveen (London: British Museum, 1977), no. 93., folio <locus n="24r"/>.</filiation>
                     
                     
                     
