                        <title xml:lang="en">Commentary on Leviticus</title>
                        
                        
                        
                        <note>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>A fragment of an Arabic commentary on Leviticus, comprising chapters 13:30-46, probably the shorter recension of the Commentary on the Pentateuch by Abu al-Faraj Furḳan. </p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Of the Hebrew text, comprising chapters 13:38-96, only the opening words of each verse are given. </p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Quotes several Karaite authorities. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        </note>
                        
                        
                        
