                           <persName xml:lang="he" key="viaf.org/viaf/58767269">ישועה בן יהודה</persName>
                        
                        
                        
                        </author>
                        
                        
                        
                        <note>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>A fragment of a commentary on Deuteronomy 31:7-13. </p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Includes a translation of verses 7-18. </p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>The Hebrew text of verses 8-13 and 14-19 (in part) is embodied, all pointed and accentuated except the last four verses. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        </note>
                        
                        
                        
                        <filiation>The translation in this manuscript agrees with Or. 2491, George Margoliouth, Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, 4 vols (London: British Museum, 1899-1935; vols I-III repr. 1965); IV, Introduction, Indexes, ed. by Jacob Leveen (London: British Museum, 1977), no. 93., folio 41r, 41v.</filiation>
                     
                     
                     
